{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"So I want to talk today about an idea. It's a big idea."},{"time":4000,"text":"Actually, I think it'll eventually"},{"time":6000,"text":"be seen as probably the single biggest idea"},{"time":8000,"text":"that's emerged in the past century."},{"time":10000,"text":"It's the idea of computation."},{"time":12000,"text":"Now, of course, that idea has brought us"},{"time":14000,"text":"all of the computer technology we have today and so on."},{"time":17000,"text":"But there's actually a lot more to computation than that."},{"time":20000,"text":"It's really a very deep, very powerful, very fundamental idea,"},{"time":23000,"text":"whose effects we've only just begun to see."}]},{"cues":[{"time":26000,"text":"Well, I myself have spent the past 30 years of my life"},{"time":29000,"text":"working on three large projects"},{"time":31000,"text":"that really try to take the idea of computation seriously."},{"time":35000,"text":"So I started off at a young age as a physicist"},{"time":38000,"text":"using computers as tools."},{"time":40000,"text":"Then, I started drilling down,"},{"time":42000,"text":"thinking about the computations I might want to do,"},{"time":44000,"text":"trying to figure out what primitives they could be built up from"},{"time":47000,"text":"and how they could be automated as much as possible."},{"time":50000,"text":"Eventually, I created a whole structure"},{"time":52000,"text":"based on symbolic programming and so on"},{"time":54000,"text":"that let me build Mathematica."},{"time":56000,"text":"And for the past 23 years, at an increasing rate,"},{"time":58000,"text":"we've been pouring more and more ideas"},{"time":60000,"text":"and capabilities and so on into Mathematica,"},{"time":62000,"text":"and I'm happy to say that that's led to many good things"},{"time":65000,"text":"in R &amp; D and education,"},{"time":67000,"text":"lots of other areas."},{"time":69000,"text":"Well, I have to admit, actually,"},{"time":71000,"text":"that I also had a very selfish reason for building Mathematica:"},{"time":74000,"text":"I wanted to use it myself,"},{"time":76000,"text":"a bit like Galileo got to use his telescope"},{"time":78000,"text":"400 years ago."},{"time":80000,"text":"But I wanted to look not at the astronomical universe,"},{"time":83000,"text":"but at the computational universe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":86000,"text":"So we normally think of programs as being"},{"time":88000,"text":"complicated things that we build"},{"time":90000,"text":"for very specific purposes."},{"time":92000,"text":"But what about the space of all possible programs?"},{"time":95000,"text":"Here's a representation of a really simple program."},{"time":98000,"text":"So, if we run this program,"},{"time":100000,"text":"this is what we get."},{"time":102000,"text":"Very simple."},{"time":104000,"text":"So let's try changing the rule"},{"time":106000,"text":"for this program a little bit."},{"time":108000,"text":"Now we get another result,"},{"time":110000,"text":"still very simple."},{"time":112000,"text":"Try changing it again."},{"time":115000,"text":"You get something a little bit more complicated."},{"time":117000,"text":"But if we keep running this for a while,"},{"time":119000,"text":"we find out that although the pattern we get is very intricate,"},{"time":122000,"text":"it has a very regular structure."},{"time":125000,"text":"So the question is: Can anything else happen?"},{"time":128000,"text":"Well, we can do a little experiment."},{"time":130000,"text":"Let's just do a little mathematical experiment, try and find out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":134000,"text":"Let's just run all possible programs"},{"time":137000,"text":"of the particular type that we're looking at."},{"time":139000,"text":"They're called cellular automata."},{"time":141000,"text":"You can see a lot of diversity in the behavior here."},{"time":143000,"text":"Most of them do very simple things,"},{"time":145000,"text":"but if you look along all these different pictures,"},{"time":147000,"text":"at rule number 30,"},{"time":149000,"text":"you start to see something interesting going on."},{"time":151000,"text":"So let's take a closer look"},{"time":153000,"text":"at rule number 30 here."},{"time":155000,"text":"So here it is."},{"time":157000,"text":"We're just following this very simple rule at the bottom here,"},{"time":160000,"text":"but we're getting all this amazing stuff."},{"time":162000,"text":"It's not at all what we're used to,"},{"time":164000,"text":"and I must say that, when I first saw this,"},{"time":166000,"text":"it came as a huge shock to my intuition."},{"time":169000,"text":"And, in fact, to understand it,"},{"time":171000,"text":"I eventually had to create"},{"time":173000,"text":"a whole new kind of science."}]},{"cues":[{"time":176000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":178000,"text":"This science is different, more general,"},{"time":181000,"text":"than the mathematics-based science that we've had"},{"time":183000,"text":"for the past 300 or so years."},{"time":186000,"text":"You know, it's always seemed like a big mystery:"},{"time":188000,"text":"how nature, seemingly so effortlessly,"},{"time":191000,"text":"manages to produce so much"},{"time":193000,"text":"that seems to us so complex."},{"time":196000,"text":"Well, I think we've found its secret:"},{"time":199000,"text":"It's just sampling what's out there in the computational universe"},{"time":202000,"text":"and quite often getting things like Rule 30"},{"time":205000,"text":"or like this."},{"time":209000,"text":"And knowing that starts to explain"},{"time":211000,"text":"a lot of long-standing mysteries in science."},{"time":214000,"text":"It also brings up new issues, though,"},{"time":216000,"text":"like computational irreducibility."},{"time":219000,"text":"I mean, we're used to having science let us predict things,"},{"time":222000,"text":"but something like this"},{"time":224000,"text":"is fundamentally irreducible."},{"time":226000,"text":"The only way to find its outcome"},{"time":228000,"text":"is, effectively, just to watch it evolve."},{"time":231000,"text":"It's connected to, what I call,"},{"time":233000,"text":"the principle of computational equivalence,"},{"time":235000,"text":"which tells us that even incredibly simple systems"},{"time":238000,"text":"can do computations as sophisticated as anything."},{"time":241000,"text":"It doesn't take lots of technology or biological evolution"},{"time":244000,"text":"to be able to do arbitrary computation;"},{"time":246000,"text":"just something that happens, naturally,"},{"time":248000,"text":"all over the place."},{"time":250000,"text":"Things with rules as simple as these can do it."},{"time":254000,"text":"Well, this has deep implications"},{"time":256000,"text":"about the limits of science,"},{"time":258000,"text":"about predictability and controllability"},{"time":260000,"text":"of things like biological processes or economies,"},{"time":263000,"text":"about intelligence in the universe,"},{"time":265000,"text":"about questions like free will"},{"time":267000,"text":"and about creating technology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":270000,"text":"You know, in working on this science for many years,"},{"time":272000,"text":"I kept wondering,"},{"time":274000,"text":"\"What will be its first killer app?\""},{"time":276000,"text":"Well, ever since I was a kid,"},{"time":278000,"text":"I'd been thinking about systematizing knowledge"},{"time":280000,"text":"and somehow making it computable."},{"time":282000,"text":"People like Leibniz had wondered about that too"},{"time":284000,"text":"300 years earlier."},{"time":286000,"text":"But I'd always assumed that to make progress,"},{"time":288000,"text":"I'd essentially have to replicate a whole brain."},{"time":291000,"text":"Well, then I got to thinking:"},{"time":293000,"text":"This scientific paradigm of mine suggests something different --"},{"time":296000,"text":"and, by the way, I've now got"},{"time":298000,"text":"huge computation capabilities in Mathematica,"},{"time":301000,"text":"and I'm a CEO with some worldly resources"},{"time":304000,"text":"to do large, seemingly crazy, projects --"},{"time":307000,"text":"So I decided to just try to see"},{"time":309000,"text":"how much of the systematic knowledge that's out there in the world"},{"time":312000,"text":"we could make computable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":314000,"text":"So, it's been a big, very complex project,"},{"time":316000,"text":"which I was not sure was going to work at all."},{"time":319000,"text":"But I'm happy to say it's actually going really well."},{"time":322000,"text":"And last year we were able"},{"time":324000,"text":"to release the first website version"},{"time":326000,"text":"of Wolfram Alpha."},{"time":328000,"text":"Its purpose is to be a serious knowledge engine"},{"time":331000,"text":"that computes answers to questions."},{"time":334000,"text":"So let's give it a try."},{"time":336000,"text":"Let's start off with something really easy."},{"time":338000,"text":"Hope for the best."},{"time":340000,"text":"Very good. Okay."},{"time":342000,"text":"So far so good."},{"time":344000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":347000,"text":"Let's try something a little bit harder."},{"time":350000,"text":"Let's do"},{"time":352000,"text":"some mathy thing,"},{"time":355000,"text":"and with luck it'll work out the answer"},{"time":358000,"text":"and try and tell us some interesting things"},{"time":360000,"text":"things about related math."},{"time":362000,"text":"We could ask it something about the real world."},{"time":365000,"text":"Let's say -- I don't know --"},{"time":367000,"text":"what's the GDP of Spain?"},{"time":370000,"text":"And it should be able to tell us that."},{"time":372000,"text":"Now we could compute something related to this,"},{"time":374000,"text":"let's say ... the GDP of Spain"},{"time":376000,"text":"divided by, I don't know,"},{"time":378000,"text":"the -- hmmm ..."},{"time":380000,"text":"let's say the revenue of Microsoft."}]},{"cues":[{"time":382000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":384000,"text":"The idea is that we can just type this in,"},{"time":386000,"text":"this kind of question in, however we think of it."},{"time":389000,"text":"So let's try asking a question,"},{"time":391000,"text":"like a health related question."},{"time":393000,"text":"So let's say we have a lab finding that ..."},{"time":396000,"text":"you know, we have an LDL level of 140"},{"time":398000,"text":"for a male aged 50."},{"time":401000,"text":"So let's type that in, and now Wolfram Alpha"},{"time":403000,"text":"will go and use available public health data"},{"time":405000,"text":"and try and figure out"},{"time":407000,"text":"what part of the population that corresponds to and so on."},{"time":410000,"text":"Or let's try asking about, I don't know,"},{"time":413000,"text":"the International Space Station."}]},{"cues":[{"time":415000,"text":"And what's happening here is that"},{"time":417000,"text":"Wolfram Alpha is not just looking up something;"},{"time":419000,"text":"it's computing, in real time,"},{"time":422000,"text":"where the International Space Station is right now at this moment,"},{"time":425000,"text":"how fast it's going, and so on."},{"time":429000,"text":"So Wolfram Alpha knows about lots and lots of kinds of things."},{"time":432000,"text":"It's got, by now,"},{"time":434000,"text":"pretty good coverage of everything you might find"},{"time":436000,"text":"in a standard reference library."},{"time":439000,"text":"But the goal is to go much further"},{"time":441000,"text":"and, very broadly, to democratize"},{"time":444000,"text":"all of this knowledge,"},{"time":447000,"text":"and to try and be an authoritative"},{"time":449000,"text":"source in all areas."},{"time":451000,"text":"To be able to compute answers to specific questions that people have,"},{"time":454000,"text":"not by searching what other people"},{"time":456000,"text":"may have written down before,"},{"time":458000,"text":"but by using built in knowledge"},{"time":460000,"text":"to compute fresh new answers to specific questions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":463000,"text":"Now, of course, Wolfram Alpha"},{"time":465000,"text":"is a monumentally huge, long-term project"},{"time":467000,"text":"with lots and lots of challenges."},{"time":469000,"text":"For a start, one has to curate a zillion"},{"time":472000,"text":"different sources of facts and data,"},{"time":475000,"text":"and we built quite a pipeline of Mathematica automation"},{"time":478000,"text":"and human domain experts for doing this."},{"time":481000,"text":"But that's just the beginning."},{"time":483000,"text":"Given raw facts or data"},{"time":485000,"text":"to actually answer questions,"},{"time":487000,"text":"one has to compute:"},{"time":489000,"text":"one has to implement all those methods and models"},{"time":491000,"text":"and algorithms and so on"},{"time":493000,"text":"that science and other areas have built up over the centuries."},{"time":496000,"text":"Well, even starting from Mathematica,"},{"time":499000,"text":"this is still a huge amount of work."},{"time":501000,"text":"So far, there are about 8 million lines"},{"time":503000,"text":"of Mathematica code in Wolfram Alpha"},{"time":505000,"text":"built by experts from many, many different fields."}]},{"cues":[{"time":508000,"text":"Well, a crucial idea of Wolfram Alpha"},{"time":511000,"text":"is that you can just ask it questions"},{"time":513000,"text":"using ordinary human language,"},{"time":516000,"text":"which means that we've got to be able to take"},{"time":518000,"text":"all those strange utterances that people type into the input field"},{"time":521000,"text":"and understand them."},{"time":523000,"text":"And I must say that I thought that step"},{"time":525000,"text":"might just be plain impossible."},{"time":529000,"text":"Two big things happened:"},{"time":531000,"text":"First, a bunch of new ideas about linguistics"},{"time":534000,"text":"that came from studying the computational universe;"},{"time":537000,"text":"and second, the realization that having actual computable knowledge"},{"time":540000,"text":"completely changes how one can"},{"time":542000,"text":"set about understanding language."},{"time":545000,"text":"And, of course, now"},{"time":547000,"text":"with Wolfram Alpha actually out in the wild,"},{"time":549000,"text":"we can learn from its actual usage."},{"time":551000,"text":"And, in fact, there's been"},{"time":553000,"text":"an interesting coevolution that's been going on"},{"time":555000,"text":"between Wolfram Alpha"},{"time":557000,"text":"and its human users,"},{"time":559000,"text":"and it's really encouraging."},{"time":561000,"text":"Right now, if we look at web queries,"},{"time":563000,"text":"more than 80 percent of them get handled successfully the first time."},{"time":566000,"text":"And if you look at things like the iPhone app,"},{"time":568000,"text":"the fraction is considerably larger."},{"time":570000,"text":"So, I'm pretty pleased with it all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":572000,"text":"But, in many ways,"},{"time":574000,"text":"we're still at the very beginning with Wolfram Alpha."},{"time":577000,"text":"I mean, everything is scaling up very nicely"},{"time":579000,"text":"and we're getting more confident."},{"time":581000,"text":"You can expect to see Wolfram Alpha technology"},{"time":583000,"text":"showing up in more and more places,"},{"time":585000,"text":"working both with this kind of public data, like on the website,"},{"time":588000,"text":"and with private knowledge"},{"time":590000,"text":"for people and companies and so on."},{"time":593000,"text":"You know, I've realized that Wolfram Alpha actually gives one"},{"time":596000,"text":"a whole new kind of computing"},{"time":598000,"text":"that one can call knowledge-based computing,"},{"time":600000,"text":"in which one's starting not just from raw computation,"},{"time":603000,"text":"but from a vast amount of built-in knowledge."},{"time":606000,"text":"And when one does that, one really changes"},{"time":608000,"text":"the economics of delivering computational things,"},{"time":611000,"text":"whether it's on the web or elsewhere."}]},{"cues":[{"time":613000,"text":"You know, we have a fairly interesting situation right now."},{"time":616000,"text":"On the one hand, we have Mathematica,"},{"time":618000,"text":"with its sort of precise, formal language"},{"time":621000,"text":"and a huge network"},{"time":623000,"text":"of carefully designed capabilities"},{"time":625000,"text":"able to get a lot done in just a few lines."},{"time":628000,"text":"Let me show you a couple of examples here."},{"time":632000,"text":"So here's a trivial piece of Mathematica programming."},{"time":636000,"text":"Here's something where we're sort of"},{"time":638000,"text":"integrating a bunch of different capabilities here."},{"time":641000,"text":"Here we'll just create, in this line,"},{"time":644000,"text":"a little user interface that allows us to"},{"time":647000,"text":"do something fun there."},{"time":650000,"text":"If you go on, that's a slightly more complicated program"},{"time":652000,"text":"that's now doing all sorts of algorithmic things"},{"time":655000,"text":"and creating user interface and so on."},{"time":657000,"text":"But it's something that is very precise stuff."},{"time":660000,"text":"It's a precise specification with a precise formal language"},{"time":663000,"text":"that causes Mathematica to know what to do here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":666000,"text":"Then on the other hand, we have Wolfram Alpha,"},{"time":669000,"text":"with all the messiness of the world"},{"time":671000,"text":"and human language and so on built into it."},{"time":673000,"text":"So what happens when you put these things together?"},{"time":676000,"text":"I think it's actually rather wonderful."},{"time":678000,"text":"With Wolfram Alpha inside Mathematica,"},{"time":680000,"text":"you can, for example, make precise programs"},{"time":682000,"text":"that call on real world data."},{"time":684000,"text":"Here's a real simple example."},{"time":689000,"text":"You can also just sort of give vague input"},{"time":692000,"text":"and then try and have Wolfram Alpha"},{"time":694000,"text":"figure out what you're talking about."},{"time":696000,"text":"Let's try this here."},{"time":698000,"text":"But actually I think the most exciting thing about this"},{"time":701000,"text":"is that it really gives one the chance"},{"time":703000,"text":"to democratize programming."},{"time":706000,"text":"I mean, anyone will be able to say what they want in plain language."},{"time":709000,"text":"Then, the idea is that Wolfram Alpha will be able to figure out"},{"time":712000,"text":"what precise pieces of code"},{"time":714000,"text":"can do what they're asking for"},{"time":716000,"text":"and then show them examples that will let them pick what they need"},{"time":719000,"text":"to build up bigger and bigger, precise programs."},{"time":722000,"text":"So, sometimes, Wolfram Alpha"},{"time":724000,"text":"will be able to do the whole thing immediately"},{"time":726000,"text":"and just give back a whole big program that you can then compute with."},{"time":729000,"text":"Here's a big website"},{"time":731000,"text":"where we've been collecting lots of educational"},{"time":734000,"text":"and other demonstrations about lots of kinds of things."},{"time":737000,"text":"I'll show you one example here."},{"time":741000,"text":"This is just an example of one of these computable documents."},{"time":744000,"text":"This is probably a fairly small"},{"time":746000,"text":"piece of Mathematica code"},{"time":748000,"text":"that's able to be run here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":752000,"text":"Okay. Let's zoom out again."},{"time":755000,"text":"So, given our new kind of science,"},{"time":757000,"text":"is there a general way to use it to make technology?"},{"time":760000,"text":"So, with physical materials,"},{"time":762000,"text":"we're used to going around the world"},{"time":764000,"text":"and discovering that particular materials"},{"time":766000,"text":"are useful for particular"},{"time":768000,"text":"technological purposes."},{"time":770000,"text":"Well, it turns out we can do very much the same kind of thing"},{"time":772000,"text":"in the computational universe."},{"time":774000,"text":"There's an inexhaustible supply of programs out there."},{"time":777000,"text":"The challenge is to see how to"},{"time":779000,"text":"harness them for human purposes."},{"time":781000,"text":"Something like Rule 30, for example,"},{"time":783000,"text":"turns out to be a really good randomness generator."},{"time":785000,"text":"Other simple programs are good models"},{"time":787000,"text":"for processes in the natural or social world."},{"time":790000,"text":"And, for example, Wolfram Alpha and Mathematica"},{"time":792000,"text":"are actually now full of algorithms"},{"time":794000,"text":"that we discovered by searching the computational universe."},{"time":798000,"text":"And, for example, this -- if we go back here --"},{"time":802000,"text":"this has become surprisingly popular"},{"time":804000,"text":"among composers"},{"time":806000,"text":"finding musical forms by searching the computational universe."},{"time":810000,"text":"In a sense, we can use the computational universe"},{"time":812000,"text":"to get mass customized creativity."},{"time":815000,"text":"I'm hoping we can, for example,"},{"time":817000,"text":"use that even to get Wolfram Alpha"},{"time":819000,"text":"to routinely do invention and discovery on the fly,"},{"time":822000,"text":"and to find all sorts of wonderful stuff"},{"time":824000,"text":"that no engineer"},{"time":826000,"text":"and no process of incremental evolution would ever come up with."}]},{"cues":[{"time":830000,"text":"Well, so, that leads to kind of an ultimate question:"},{"time":833000,"text":"Could it be that someplace out there in the computational universe"},{"time":836000,"text":"we might find our physical universe?"},{"time":839000,"text":"Perhaps there's even some quite simple rule,"},{"time":841000,"text":"some simple program for our universe."},{"time":844000,"text":"Well, the history of physics would have us believe"},{"time":846000,"text":"that the rule for the universe must be pretty complicated."},{"time":849000,"text":"But in the computational universe,"},{"time":851000,"text":"we've now seen how rules that are incredibly simple"},{"time":854000,"text":"can produce incredibly rich and complex behavior."},{"time":857000,"text":"So could that be what's going on with our whole universe?"},{"time":861000,"text":"If the rules for the universe are simple,"},{"time":863000,"text":"it's kind of inevitable that they have to be"},{"time":865000,"text":"very abstract and very low level;"},{"time":867000,"text":"operating, for example, far below"},{"time":869000,"text":"the level of space or time,"},{"time":871000,"text":"which makes it hard to represent things."},{"time":873000,"text":"But in at least a large class of cases,"},{"time":875000,"text":"one can think of the universe as being"},{"time":877000,"text":"like some kind of network,"},{"time":879000,"text":"which, when it gets big enough,"},{"time":881000,"text":"behaves like continuous space"},{"time":883000,"text":"in much the same way as having lots of molecules"},{"time":885000,"text":"can behave like a continuous fluid."},{"time":887000,"text":"Well, then the universe has to evolve by applying"},{"time":890000,"text":"little rules that progressively update this network."},{"time":893000,"text":"And each possible rule, in a sense,"},{"time":895000,"text":"corresponds to a candidate universe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":897000,"text":"Actually, I haven't shown these before,"},{"time":901000,"text":"but here are a few of the candidate universes"},{"time":904000,"text":"that I've looked at."},{"time":906000,"text":"Some of these are hopeless universes,"},{"time":908000,"text":"completely sterile,"},{"time":910000,"text":"with other kinds of pathologies like no notion of space,"},{"time":912000,"text":"no notion of time, no matter,"},{"time":915000,"text":"other problems like that."},{"time":917000,"text":"But the exciting thing that I've found in the last few years"},{"time":920000,"text":"is that you actually don't have to go very far"},{"time":922000,"text":"in the computational universe"},{"time":924000,"text":"before you start finding candidate universes"},{"time":926000,"text":"that aren't obviously not our universe."},{"time":929000,"text":"Here's the problem:"},{"time":931000,"text":"Any serious candidate for our universe"},{"time":934000,"text":"is inevitably full of computational irreducibility."},{"time":937000,"text":"Which means that it is irreducibly difficult"},{"time":940000,"text":"to find out how it will really behave,"},{"time":942000,"text":"and whether it matches our physical universe."},{"time":946000,"text":"A few years ago, I was pretty excited to discover"},{"time":949000,"text":"that there are candidate universes with incredibly simple rules"},{"time":952000,"text":"that successfully reproduce special relativity,"},{"time":954000,"text":"and even general relativity and gravitation,"},{"time":957000,"text":"and at least give hints of quantum mechanics."},{"time":960000,"text":"So, will we find the whole of physics?"},{"time":962000,"text":"I don't know for sure,"},{"time":964000,"text":"but I think at this point it's sort of"},{"time":966000,"text":"almost embarrassing not to at least try."}]},{"cues":[{"time":968000,"text":"Not an easy project."},{"time":970000,"text":"One's got to build a lot of technology."},{"time":972000,"text":"One's got to build a structure that's probably"},{"time":974000,"text":"at least as deep as existing physics."},{"time":976000,"text":"And I'm not sure what the best way to organize the whole thing is."},{"time":979000,"text":"Build a team, open it up, offer prizes and so on."},{"time":982000,"text":"But I'll tell you, here today,"},{"time":984000,"text":"that I'm committed to seeing this project done,"},{"time":986000,"text":"to see if, within this decade,"},{"time":989000,"text":"we can finally hold in our hands"},{"time":991000,"text":"the rule for our universe"},{"time":993000,"text":"and know where our universe lies"},{"time":995000,"text":"in the space of all possible universes ..."},{"time":997000,"text":"and be able to type into Wolfram Alpha, \"the theory of the universe,\""},{"time":1000000,"text":"and have it tell us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1002000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1005000,"text":"So I've been working on the idea of computation"},{"time":1007000,"text":"now for more than 30 years,"},{"time":1009000,"text":"building tools and methods and turning intellectual ideas"},{"time":1012000,"text":"into millions of lines of code"},{"time":1014000,"text":"and grist for server farms and so on."},{"time":1016000,"text":"With every passing year,"},{"time":1018000,"text":"I realize how much more powerful"},{"time":1020000,"text":"the idea of computation really is."},{"time":1022000,"text":"It's taken us a long way already,"},{"time":1024000,"text":"but there's so much more to come."},{"time":1026000,"text":"From the foundations of science"},{"time":1028000,"text":"to the limits of technology"},{"time":1030000,"text":"to the very definition of the human condition,"},{"time":1032000,"text":"I think computation is destined to be"},{"time":1034000,"text":"the defining idea of our future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1036000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1038000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1052000,"text":"Chris Anderson: That was astonishing."},{"time":1054000,"text":"Stay here. I've got a question."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1056000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1062000,"text":"So, that was, fair to say, an astonishing talk."},{"time":1066000,"text":"Are you able to say in a sentence or two"},{"time":1069000,"text":"how this type of thinking"},{"time":1072000,"text":"could integrate at some point"},{"time":1074000,"text":"to things like string theory or the kind of things that people think of"},{"time":1076000,"text":"as the fundamental explanations of the universe?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1079000,"text":"Stephen Wolfram: Well, the parts of physics"},{"time":1081000,"text":"that we kind of know to be true,"},{"time":1083000,"text":"things like the standard model of physics:"},{"time":1085000,"text":"what I'm trying to do better reproduce the standard model of physics"},{"time":1088000,"text":"or it's simply wrong."},{"time":1090000,"text":"The things that people have tried to do in the last 25 years or so"},{"time":1092000,"text":"with string theory and so on"},{"time":1094000,"text":"have been an interesting exploration"},{"time":1096000,"text":"that has tried to get back to the standard model,"},{"time":1099000,"text":"but hasn't quite gotten there."},{"time":1101000,"text":"My guess is that some great simplifications of what I'm doing"},{"time":1104000,"text":"may actually have considerable resonance"},{"time":1107000,"text":"with what's been done in string theory,"},{"time":1109000,"text":"but that's a complicated math thing"},{"time":1112000,"text":"that I don't yet know how it's going to work out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1115000,"text":"CA: Benoit Mandelbrot is in the audience."},{"time":1117000,"text":"He also has shown how complexity"},{"time":1119000,"text":"can arise out of a simple start."},{"time":1121000,"text":"Does your work relate to his?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1123000,"text":"SW: I think so."},{"time":1125000,"text":"I view Benoit Mandelbrot's work"},{"time":1127000,"text":"as one of the founding contributions"},{"time":1130000,"text":"to this kind of area."},{"time":1133000,"text":"Benoit has been particularly interested"},{"time":1135000,"text":"in nested patterns, in fractals and so on,"},{"time":1137000,"text":"where the structure is something"},{"time":1139000,"text":"that's kind of tree-like,"},{"time":1141000,"text":"and where there's sort of a big branch that makes little branches"},{"time":1143000,"text":"and even smaller branches and so on."},{"time":1146000,"text":"That's one of the ways"},{"time":1148000,"text":"that you get towards true complexity."},{"time":1151000,"text":"I think things like the Rule 30 cellular automaton"},{"time":1154000,"text":"get us to a different level."},{"time":1156000,"text":"In fact, in a very precise way, they get us to a different level"},{"time":1159000,"text":"because they seem to be things that are"},{"time":1162000,"text":"capable of complexity"},{"time":1165000,"text":"that's sort of as great as complexity can ever get ..."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1169000,"text":"I could go on about this at great length, but I won't. (Laughter) (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1172000,"text":"CA: Stephen Wolfram, thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1174000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}